I ordered Combo #3 from El Emperador Elias. This plate comes with a portion of beans, by which I found dead maggots mixed in. I was completely horrified at the fact that my husband and I found at least 20 dead maggots. We served this to our five-year-old daughter and noticed after the fact. This is especially alarming because our daughter has been sick. Upon calling the restaurant, El Emperador Elias staff was rude and completely unapologetic. They barely acknowledged that they had served food with maggots and accused us of lying. We were denied a refund, and needless to say an apology. This is completely unprofessional and abusive. We will not be ordering from this restaurant ever again and advise everybody to be wary of the food. We suggest checking your orders before serving and consuming the food.  Please refer to the pictures provided. You can clearly see the maggots covered in the bean sauce. We even washed the maggots to clearly see them.

One of the worst restaurants to order from for delivery. No matter how many times I have placed an order for delivery, this restaurant fails to follow through. Tonight I placed an order at 6:30 pm that stated it would be delivered by 7:30 pm. At 8:20 pm I called and the woman who answered stated the driver was out for delivery. At 8:40, we called again and she stated still that order was out for delivery. At 9:11 pm, I called again and again she stated order would arrive in 3 minutes even though their kitchen closes at 9:00 pm. Finally, I contacted a GrubHub agent who reached out. The restaurant advised the agent the order was never received and my order was canceled.  This isn’t the first time I have had this problem with Emperador Elias. Great restaurant to go to but as far as delivery they are horrible and let’s not even talk about the lack of great customer service they have. Unbelievable that they would offer this delivery service and can not actually even accommodate it. Let’s not even discuss the lies. Just be open and say you don’t have the order. Elias is one of my all time favorite places. This is usually my last stop when I am pulling an all nighter. It is also good for an early night dinner and drinks with a friend. Elias never disappoints! The mojitos are always made to perfection. The food is consistently delicious no matter the time of the day. I have found myself enjoying creamy shrimp mofongo, grilled salmon w/tostones, and avocado pyramid salad among many other plates at 5 am. I love the ambiance at Elias; it is always packed with happy people. Friday and Saturday nights are the best! Walking in here during karaoke will make you feel like you are at American Idol. The regulars who frequent the mic are people with spectacular voices. Space wise is perfect for what it is; not too small not too big. They have hookah for the hookah lovers. The reason why I can't give it 5 stars is due to the sad bathroom situation. It's one bathroom and it is always filthy. On a more positive note, that soon will be resolved once they're done with renovations on the second bathroom. I highly recommend Elias if you are looking to enjoy great food, music, and a good crowd.
